---
layout: layout.njk
title: Home
showTitle: false
---
<section class="home-lead">
  <p class="lede-mark">woodson42.com</p>
  <h1>Notes written slowly.</h1>
  <p>
    Derek Sivers' site works because it refuses decoration and trusts writing,
    pacing, and typography to do the job. This version borrows that restraint:
    a narrow reading column, visible dates, blue links, and enough warmth in
    the page to feel kept rather than generated.
  </p>
</section>

<section aria-labelledby="archive-heading">
  <div class="archive-head">
    <h2 id="archive-heading">Archive</h2>
    <p>{{ collections.posts | length }} essay{% if collections.posts | length != 1 %}s{% endif %}</p>
  </div>

  <ol class="essay-list">
    {% for post in collections.posts | reverse %}
      <li>
        <time datetime="{{ post.date | htmlDateString }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time>
        <a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
      </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ol>
</section>
